    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Machines used for macerating rags into pulp for papermaking. Named for their country of origin, they appeared in Germany as early as 1710.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
